o find the time to compose, his turbulent and complex sexuality, his political activities, and his endless capacity for hard work. Beyond all this, these writings provide a glimpse of the man behind the legends: his humanity, warmth, volatility, intellectual brilliance, wonderful eye for descriptive detail, and humor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBernstein, Leonard, -- 1918-1990 -- Correspondence. 0aComposers -- United States -- Correspondence. 0aComposerszUnited StatesvCorrespondence. 0aConductors (Music) -- United States -- Correspondence. 0aConductors (Music)zUnited StatesvCorrespondence. 0aMusicians -- United States -- Correspondence. 0aMusicianszUnited StatesvCorrespondence. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh1 aSimeone, Nigel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018654340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300186543423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300186543/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles